      • syncComputedValues

        void syncComputedValues()
        This base class implementation updates all the CoveredState. Subclasses may update their own particular computed values.

        This method is typically called at "key" points in the lifecycle of a policy, such as just before quoting and just before issuance.

        See Also:
        PolicyPeriod.syncComputedValues()

      • canSafelyDeleteLocation

        java.lang.String canSafelyDeleteLocation(PolicyLocation location)
        Indicates whether or not this location can be safely deleted, according to this policy line. If this returns a null or empty string, that means that the line thinks it's okay to delete the location. Otherwise, this method should return an error message indicating why the location can't be deleted.

        Depending on the line, it may be possible to safely delete a location even if it is in use.

        Parameters:
        location - the PolicyLocation to check
        Returns:
        an error message if it can't be safely deleted, null or the empty String if it can

      • canSafelyDeleteNamedInsured

        java.lang.String canSafelyDeleteNamedInsured(PolicyNamedInsured polNamedInsured)
        Indicates whether or not this policy named insured can be safely deleted, according to this policy line. If this returns a null or empty string, that means that the line thinks it's okay to delete the policy named insured. Otherwise, this method should return an error message indicating why the policy named insured can't be deleted.
        Parameters:
        polNamedInsured - the PolicyNamedInsured to check
        Returns:
        an error message if it can't be safely deleted, null or the empty String if it can

      • canSafelyDeleteExistingContact

        java.lang.String canSafelyDeleteExistingContact(Contact toContact)
        Indicates whether or not this contact can be safely deleted, according to this policy line. If this returns a null or empty string, that means that the line thinks it's okay to delete this contact. Otherwise, this method should return an error message indicating why this contact can't be deleted.
        Parameters:
        toContact - the contact to check
        Returns:
        an error message if it can't be safely deleted, null or the empty String if it can

      • isUnusedLocationCleanupEnabled

        boolean isUnusedLocationCleanupEnabled()
        Indicates if unused location cleanup is enabled for this line of business. If true, the quote process for any transaction on a policy that includes this line of business will detect and remove unused locations.
        Returns:
        true if the policy line has enabled unused location cleanup, false if it has not.

      • checkLocationInUse

        @Deprecated
boolean checkLocationInUse(PolicyLocation location)
        Deprecated. In 10.0.0 and will be removed in 11.0.0. Please use getLocationsInUseOnOrAfterSliceDate(). If you currently have an overriding Line-of-Business-specific implementation, please override getLocationsInUseOnOrAfterSliceDate() instead.
        Indicates whether or not this location is in use by the policy line.

        Depending on the line, it may be possible to safely delete a location even if it is in use.

        Parameters:
        location - the PolicyLocation to check
        Returns:
        true if the PolicyLocation is in use by this line, false if it is not

      • usesAllOOSSliceDates

        boolean usesAllOOSSliceDates()
        Determines if this line supports all OOS slice dates instead of only bound edit effective dates.
        Returns:

      • isWorkersComp

        boolean isWorkersComp()
        Marks lines that are WorkersComp lines. OOTB this is only the WCLine.
        Returns:
        true: Is a WorkersComp line.

      • shouldParallelizeRating

        boolean shouldParallelizeRating()
        Returns false for lines not supporting parallelization, true for lines supporting parallelization, or -- depending on the implementation -- conditionally true for lines which support parallelization yet sometimes restrict it. In the base configuration, the abstract implementation of this method returns false and must be overridden by each line that supports parallelization.

      • isAPDLine

        boolean isAPDLine()
        Marks the PolicyLine as generated by APD. False for OOTB lines of business
        Returns:
        true: Is APD Generated Line
